success - this operation never fails.

5f8e45db-bcfe-4ba8-91a5-7376424b8c76.description=
Synopsis

    This flow creates an export rule based on the atlas configuration file.
    export-rule-create performs the following steps\:
      1. Review the atlas configuration file.
      2. Pull the variable information from the configuration file template.
      3. Format the variables for the export rule.
      4. Pass the information back to the requesting entity.

Inputs

    api - The application programming interface (API) includes the protocol specifications (required).
    tier - The tier is the Quality of Service (QoS) offering for the product (e.g. vital, velocity, or value). The volume is assigned a storage tier that correlates to a service level and
             performance guarantee (required).
    confVarList - The configuration variable list is a list of variables that make up the configuration of Unified Storage products (required).
    confFilePath - The configuration file path is the path to access the configuration file (required).
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: None.

    overrideJRAS - Value to override the system-defined Java RAS server.
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: Hosting Eng RAS.

Results

    hpooFlowResult - The XML response specific to the functionality of the flow; in this case creating an export rule. See Notes section for more details.
    flowStatus - Overall status of the flow, value is one of the string literals "success" or "failed".

Responses

    Success - All operations and subflows completed successfully.
    Failure - Some operations and/or subflows failed.

Notes

    1. Anything else the caller or support person may need to know about the flow. Relationships that aren't easily inferred, abmnormal flow behaviors, hard-codings, etc.
